5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR SPEECH-LANGUAGE PATHOLOGY AIDES
6 AND AUDIOLOGY AIDES; PROVIDING THAT A SPEECH-LANGUAGE PATHOLOGY AIDE OR AUDIOLOGY
7 AIDE IS NOT REQUIRED TO BE LICENSED; PROVIDING REQUIREMENTS FOR A SPEECH-LANGUAGE
8 PATHOLOGY AIDE OR AUDIOLOGY AIDE; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AND AMENDING
9 SECTION 37-15-301, MCA.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 37-15-301, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "37-15-301. License required -- exception -- rulemaking. (1) A license must be issued to qualified
15 persons either in speech-language pathology or audiology. A person may be licensed in both areas if the
16 person meets the respective qualifications, and in those instances, the license fee must be as though for one
17 license.
18 (2) A person may not practice or represent to the public that the person is a speech-language
19 pathologist, an audiologist, a speech-language pathology assistant, or an audiology assistant in this state
20 unless the person is licensed in accordance with the provisions of this chapter.
21 (3) The board may issue a limited license to qualified individuals engaged in supervised
22 professional experience, as defined by board rule.
23 (4) The board shall establish by rule the qualifications and scope of work for speech-language
24 pathology aides and audiology aides. A speech-language pathology aide or audiology aide:
25 (a) is not required to be licensed by the board;
26 (b) shall work under the supervision of a speech-language pathologist or an audiologist a minimum
27 of 20% of the time; and
28 (c) may not perform work that requires the independent judgment of a speech-language
